## Launch Timeline

* Ad copies/KWs translation done 4 weeks before launch date
* Stakeholder approval and edit done 3 weeks before launch date
* Launch timeline will be dependent on time of PR go live
* MCS site goes live
* +2hrs: Paid Search Ads goes live [5 hours before PR launch to ensure ads are public
* PR/Comms goes live at set time
    * Example - MCS site goes live at 12am CST. Paid Search goes live at 2am CST. PR/Comms goes out at 7am CST.


**On Launch**

* If ads are disapproved from MCS not being live pre-launch, change Final URL for ads then change it to the correct URL again. Do NOT appeal ads and wait for approval as that will take several hours to days. Editing the ads will be approved much quicker
* Assure traffic is coming in as expected.
* Communicate successful launch with stakeholders.
* Check for regs 2 days after launch via Hubble and validate they are coming into Adobe.



